\fs36 \cf0 Task 1: V-Model Mapping\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 1. V-Model\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0                   SDLC                          TDLC\
\
           Requirements  ---------------->  Acceptance Testing\
\
             System Design  ------------->  System Testing\
\
         Architecture Design ----------->  Integration Testing\
\
             Module Design  ------------->  Unit Testing\
\
                      Coding
\f2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
Coding is the bottom point of the V-Model. Development activities are performed on the left side, while the corresponding testing activities are carried out on the right side.\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 2. SDLC Phase and Corresponding Test Artifact\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Requirements Phase\
Corresponding Testing Phase:\uc0\u8232 Acceptance Testing\
Test Artifact Produced:\uc0\u8232 Acceptance Test Plan and Acceptance Test Cases are prepared based on business requirements.\
\
System Design Phase\
Corresponding Testing Phase:\uc0\u8232 System Testing\
Test Artifact Produced:\uc0\u8232 System Test Plan and System Test Cases are prepared to validate the complete system.\
\
Architecture Design Phase\
Corresponding Testing Phase:\uc0\u8232 Integration Testing\
Test Artifact Produced:\uc0\u8232 Integration Test Plan and Integration Test Cases are prepared to verify interactions between different modules.\
\
Module Design Phase\
Corresponding Testing Phase:\uc0\u8232 Unit Testing\
Test Artifact Produced:\uc0\u8232 Unit Test Cases are prepared to verify individual functions and modules.\
\
Coding Phase\
Corresponding Testing Phase:\uc0\u8232 Execution of all planned tests.\
Test Artifact Produced:\uc0\u8232 Source code and executable application.\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

